I tried to inherit FEProblemBase, but that made getParams(...) ambigious, so that didn't seem right, so I only include FEProblemBase.h, not inherit from it.
I pulled some of the basic ideas from ReferenceResidualProblem.C
Thanks!

I would like to have one more question. How to implement the p*∂α_g/∂x  term in ADDGkernel? I tried to implement this by adding this term in the DGkernel (according to ADNumericalFlux3EqnDGKernel.C) in the following way:
  ADReal re = 0.0;
  switch (type)  
  {
    case Moose::Element:
      if (_equation_index == EQ_LIQUID_MOMENTUM) 
        re = (flux_elem[_equation_index] + _press_interface[_qp]*flux_elem_nonc[_equation_index]) * _test[_i][_qp];
      else if (_equation_index == EQ_VAPOUR_MOMENTUM)
        re = (flux_elem[_equation_index] - _press_interface[_qp]*flux_elem_nonc[_equation_index]) * _test[_i][_qp];
      else
        re = flux_elem[_equation_index] * _test[_i][_qp];

      break;

    case Moose::Neighbor:
      if (_equation_index == EQ_LIQUID_MOMENTUM)
        re = -(flux_neig[_equation_index] + _press_interface_neig[_qp]*flux_neig_nonc[_equation_index]) * _test_neighbor[_i][_qp];
      else if (_equation_index ==EQ_VAPOUR_MOMENTUM)
        re = -(flux_neig[_equation_index] - _press_interface_neig[_qp]*flux_neig_nonc[_equation_index]) * _test_neighbor[_i][_qp];
      else
        re = -flux_neig[_equation_index] * _test_neighbor[_i][_qp];

      break;
  }

  return re;


In this way, the p*∂α_g/∂x also used the slope limiter. Does it correct?
